service: Amazon WorkLink is a cloud-based service that provides secure access to internal websites and web apps from iOS and Android phones. In a single step, your users, such as employees, can access internal websites as efficiently as they access any other public website. They enter a URL in their web browser, or choose a link to an internal website in an email. Amazon WorkLink authenticates the user's access and securely renders authorized internal web content in a secure rendering service in the AWS cloud. Amazon WorkLink doesn't download or store any internal web content on mobile devices.

operations.AssociateDomain: Specifies a domain to be associated to Amazon WorkLink.
operations.AssociateWebsiteAuthorizationProvider: Associates a website authorization provider with a specified fleet. This is used to authorize users against associated websites in the company network.
operations.AssociateWebsiteCertificateAuthority: Imports the root certificate of a certificate authority (CA) used to obtain TLS certificates used by associated websites within the company network.
operations.CreateFleet: Creates a fleet. A fleet consists of resources and the configuration that delivers associated websites to authorized users who download and set up the Amazon WorkLink app.
operations.DeleteFleet: Deletes a fleet. Prevents users from accessing previously associated websites.
operations.DescribeAuditStreamConfiguration: Describes the configuration for delivering audit streams to the customer account.
operations.DescribeCompanyNetworkConfiguration: Describes the networking configuration to access the internal websites associated with the specified fleet.
operations.DescribeDevicePolicyConfiguration: Describes the device policy configuration for the specified fleet.
operations.DescribeFleetMetadata: Provides basic information for the specified fleet, excluding identity provider, networking, and device configuration details.
operations.DescribeIdentityProviderConfiguration: Describes the identity provider configuration of the specified fleet.
operations.DisassociateDomain: Disassociates a domain from Amazon WorkLink. End users lose the ability to access the domain with Amazon WorkLink.
operations.DisassociateWebsiteAuthorizationProvider: Disassociates a website authorization provider from a specified fleet. After the disassociation, users can't load any associated websites that require this authorization provider.
operations.ListDevices: Retrieves a list of devices registered with the specified fleet.
operations.ListDomains: Retrieves a list of domains associated to a specified fleet.
operations.ListFleets: Retrieves a list of fleets for the current account and Region.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Retrieves a list of tags for the specified resource.
operations.ListWebsiteAuthorizationProviders: Retrieves a list of website authorization providers associated with a specified fleet.
operations.ListWebsiteCertificateAuthorities: Retrieves a list of certificate authorities added for the current account and Region.
operations.RestoreDomainAccess: Moves a domain to ACTIVE status if it was in the INACTIVE status.
operations.RevokeDomainAccess: Moves a domain to INACTIVE status if it was in the ACTIVE status.
operations.SignOutUser: Signs the user out from all of their devices. The user can sign in again if they have valid credentials.
operations.TagResource: Adds or overwrites one or more tags for the specified resource, such as a fleet. Each tag consists of a key and an optional value. If a resource already has a tag with the same key, this operation updates its value.
operations.UntagResource: Removes one or more tags from the specified resource.
operations.UpdateAuditStreamConfiguration: Updates the audit stream configuration for the fleet.
operations.UpdateCompanyNetworkConfiguration: Updates the company network configuration for the fleet.
operations.UpdateDevicePolicyConfiguration: Updates the device policy configuration for the fleet.
operations.UpdateIdentityProviderConfiguration: Updates the identity provider configuration for the fleet.
